metadata.name: SoulFish #4
metadata.description:
Named after the artist Wu Che-Yu, the soul fish was born in the void and crystallized from human emotions.

Fluttering silently and slowly, their bodies almost disappeared in the light of the deep sea.
The fish swims freely, and this is the happiness of the fish.
If we are not a fish, how do we know the joy of a fish?
How do we know that we do not know the joy of fish?
We will only learn about it when we come to the riverside.

Inspired by Zhuāngzǐ: "The Debate on the Joy of Fish" c. 3rd century BC

Interactivities:
> Key S: Save
> Holding mouse in different directions: Swim 
> Click and let the fish touch the Bubbles
> Key B: Toggle border
> Key P: Pause

metadata.name: Disintegrating #8
metadata.description:
Disintegrating is an animated, interactive piece which allows the user to change the colour and luminosity of the lines within the artwork using mouse movement.

Move the mouse around the screen to see the colour changing effects.

mouseclick will stop the animation at its current state
'spacebar' will restart the animation
'r' will reset and restart the animation
'f' will set the animation to no disintegration at the current colours

Disintegrating is my first piece which includes a Webgl shader integrated with p5.js coding.

metadata.name: Elswhere #10
metadata.description:
Perlin noise walks into a Julia set and finds itself Elswhere. X is real, Y is imaginary, or is it the other way around? 

Elswhere is a unique generative art series in which noise and fractal math are combined to create whimsical shapes and motifs, with an infinite number of variations. Made with p5js.

For each pixel, the noise values corresponding to the X and Y coordinates are computed and then used as the real and imaginary components for initializing a Julia set recursion. The pixel is colored based on the number of steps it takes for the recursion to reach its base case.

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[2] Render 2000x3000px image.
[4] Render 4000x6000px image.
[6] Render 6000x9000px image.

Created by Elsif, 2022.05

metadata.name: geometric tiles #48
metadata.description:
Hello everyone, this is my first fxhash project.

There are three types of mints you can get: checkers, stairs and rectangular prisms - there is equal chance of getting any of those. 

There is also 8% chance of getting the rarity mint which is the mint with the grainy effect over it. However, you should check my twitter out in order to see the preview of all the mint types you can get.

The inspiration behind this project was M.C. Escher.

metadata.name: Tesseract #9
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.
